AGRA stalked the pace on the outside, ranged up in the three path on the turn, made a bid outside the quarter-pole, lost touch with the winner while asked for her best in upper stretch, dropped back into the final furlong and weakened. ECHO BAYBE (IRE) was hustled from the gate, tracked the leader down the backstretch, dropped back in the two path early on the turn, was roused with three furlongs to run, shifted to the three path late on that bend, came four wide into upper stretch, moved out near the three-sixteenths pole then drifted out under a left-handed crop outside the furlong marker and came up empty. STREET VIEW was urged along off the pace, went two then three wide on the turn, came five wide into the stretch, was carried out outside the furlong marker and failed to respond.
